# Prototyper Project Rules

## Project Structure
- `backend/` - FastAPI REST API
- `frontend/` - Next.js application

## General Principles
- Write clean, idiomatic code
- Follow DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Keep functions small and focused
- Write self-documenting code with clear names

## Development Workflow
- Use type safety (TypeScript for frontend, type hints for backend)
- Update API client (`frontend/lib/api.ts`) when adding backend endpoints
- Keep frontend and backend interfaces in sync
- All components are kept under components/[feature]/
- Each component is placed in a separate file; no default export

## Documentation
- Read from CLAUDE.md to get the context of the requirements of the application if available
- Add comments for complex logic only
- Update README when adding major features
- Include examples in docstrings
- Keep setup instructions current

## Code Review Standards
- All public functions must have type annotations
- New components should be reusable
- API endpoints must return proper status codes
- Error handling required for all async operations
- Use logger decorators to log major functions in the backend 

## Testing Requirements
- Write unit tests for new functions
- Test API integration end-to-end
- Validate responsive design for UI changes
- Check error states and edge cases